Second Department,

January, 1957

(January 7, 1957) Aspasia Brillis, Respondent, v. Petros Brillis, Appellant.

In an action to annul a marriage on the ground of fraud, the appeal is from a judgment (designated in the notice of appeal as an order) entered after trial in favor of respondent. Judgment unanimously affirmed, with costs. No opinion. Present — Wenzel, Acting P. J., Murphy, TJghetta, Hallinan and Kleinfeld, JJ. [207 Misc. 104.]
